Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@Lemon & Herb Seasoning{1%serving}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. When the oven is hot, bake on the
> top shelf until golden, about 25-30 mins. Turn halfway through.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel,
and chop the @Echalion shallot{1} into small pieces.

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1} (stalks and all).

Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 1cm chunks. Add the tomato chunks to a #medium
bowl{} with half the @cider vinegar{30%ml}, a drizzle of oil and the
@sugar{1/2%tsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside
for now.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking
paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #cutting board{}, then give it a bash with
the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 2-3cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken, turn the heat down to medium and cook
until golden brown, ~{7-8%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a cutting board, cover with #foil{} and
rest for a couple of mins.

Return the now-empty frying pan with a drizzle of oil (if needed) on medium
heat. Add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the
garlic and cook for ~{30%secs}.

Pour the remaining apple cider vinegar into the pan and allow it to evaporate,
~{30%secs}. Pour in the @water{100%ml} for the sauce and @chicken stock paste{10%g},
bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @butter{30%g} and parsley until the butter is melted. Simmer
until the sauce is thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Just before you are ready to serve, toss the @wild rocket{20%g} through the
dressing.

Share the chicken between your plates. Spoon over the buttery sauce. Serve with
your chips and salad alongside. Enjoy!